headline: Does GM’s Rare-Earth Magnet Move Signal More Upside for the Stock in 2025?
summary: Thinking about what to do with General Motors stock? You’re not alone. Whether you already own a few shares or you’re just sizing up the next move, the ride with GM has offered some twists, and maybe a few reasons to lean forward. Over the past year, GM is up 20.7%, and it’s delivered a remarkable 72.2% return over three years. On the flip side, the last month was a touch sluggish, dipping 2.3%, but that kind of minor turbulence is typical for automakers, especially when headlines are flying...
